ACT:
 Fundamental Rights, Infringement of-Act settling fair and equitable rent restricted to a part of the State-Settlement of rent of different localities on different dates on decennial average-Possibility of variation in rates of rent- If amount to denial of equality before law-Deprivation of landlord's right to realise rents freely and without hindrance, if invasion of right to property-Retrospective enforcement of rates of rent, if amounts to violation of right to property and acquisition without compensation-Such power conferred on Settlement Officer, if arbitrary- Constitution of India, Arts. 14, 19(1)(f), 31(2)-Marwar Land Revenue Act (XL of 1949), ss. 81, 82, 83, 84, 85, 86.
 
